node.text:
Step one, rescue vintage worn out rasp.

Step two, twist one end up a bit so you can hold onto it. (Over the horn, using tongs and a vise will make things harder)

Step 3, flatten handle out in relation to the blade and hammer the handle until it feels good in your hand. (This is where my tiny hammers come out)

Step 4, forge any blade shape you want provided you left enough blade to work with. After forging a handle, the blade will be easy!! :)

This is a technique I came up with when I started blacksmithing many years ago. I wasn't good at working with dead tree carcasses so I had to improvise. Been doing it ever since, I'm just a blacksmith after all, can't be good at everything.
By @reforgedrelics
